Great sound and it works well. I have found in the past that using these 
global equiliser apps has little effect on the bass only because when you 
put the level high it brings the volume down. However, this app has a 
loudness feature which seems to compensate for it and also I think because 
I used wired headphones and not Bluetooth in the past this also had an 
effect. My only issue is that on settings the options to hide the 
notification and the automatic on/off are greyed out. No explanation as to 
why or how to correct this. Is there a hidden FAQ somewhere to explain 
this? UPDATE: Worked out why I couldn't use those settings, it's because I 
use Amazon Music and that requires the Global Output setting to be used 
which meant that these other options aren't available. Sounds perfectly 
reasonable to me and I have tried other apps before and the EQ won't work 
at all because Amazon Music seems incompatible with them but not this app. 
Use it of you have Amazon Music. You won't go wrong. üòÅ (anyway who uses

I would love to see a button in the little menu button to restore that eq to its factory EQ as I accidentally messed with the heavy metal EQ and can't figure out how to restore without uninstalling and reinstalling.  The mixer is very responsive and versatile, you can get whatever you want out of this from low end to high end, treble to bass, and so on so it's great for me as I listen to all kinds of music!  There are also a lot of options to choose from, whether you are a fan of Blues or a Heavy Metal metalhead such as myself, to Country, pop, punk, reggae and many more! And if that isn't enough for you, you've got the option to create your own which takes advantage of your headphones or earbuds, even if they're the cheapest things on the market you could definitely trick your friends into thinking they're high quality with this app!  There are 3 major effects to choose from, bass, virtualization and loudness boost, the bass has some trouble at 100% (might depend on your earbuds or headphones quality) but otherwise easy on the ear and crisp clean sound!

I tried a lot of equalizers over the last year and many of them fell short in various ways. Some of the more popular ones ate my processing cycles and stopped applications such as Pandora while they were enabled.   I took a chance on one more, the Equalizer FX and it hit the mark with its easy to use interface, flawless operations with any of the players I use. I have N7, Google's Music player and Pandora and it works great. Pandora has been especially hard since it is a streaming player from the Internet. It does a great job.   I listen to Pandora a lot while at work connected to my speakers through the headphone jack on my Google Nexus 7 (Original). I am setup with stock 4.3, no custom kernel but I am rooted to allow for applications such as StickMount so I can use my 64 GB USB where I have a lot of music, ebooks and videos stored.   This software works the way I expect, easy, no performance hits, no stopping of applications, or other bad behaviors I have seen from others.   If you're looking for something that's easy to use and works with most players give this a try. I purchase the license after testing to remove the ads.
